{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","kind":"attribute","text":"MainActor"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"callAsyncJavaScript"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"_"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"functionBody"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","text":"String"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"arguments"},{"kind":"text","text":": ["},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","text":"String"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"Any"},{"kind":"text","text":"] = [:], "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"in"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"webView"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(cs)WKWebView","text":"WKWebView"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"completionHandler"},{"kind":"text","text":": (@"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","text":"MainActor"},{"text":" (","kind":"text"},{"text":"Result","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:s6ResultO"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"Any","kind":"keyword"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:8BrazeKit0A0C13WebViewBridgeO20ScriptMessageHandlerC5ErrorO","identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/WebViewBridge\/ScriptMessageHandler\/Error","text":"Error","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">) -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:s4Voida","text":"Void","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":")? = nil)","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["iOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The JavaScript string to use as the function body. This method treats"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the string as an anonymous JavaScript function body and calls it with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the named arguments in the "},{"code":"arguments","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" parameter."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"functionBody"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A dictionary of the arguments to pass to the function call. Each key in the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"dictionary corresponds to the name of an argument in the functionBody","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"string, and the value of that key is the value to use during the evaluation","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of the code. Supported value types are ","type":"text"},{"code":"NSNumber","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"NSString","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"NSArray","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"NSDictionary","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", or ","type":"text"},{"code":"NSNull","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". All items in an array or dictionary must also","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"be one of the supported types.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"arguments"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The web view in which the JavaScript function is executed. The web view must"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"implement the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/WebViewBridge\/ScriptMessageHandler","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}],"name":"webView"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A handler block to execute when script evaluation finishes. The"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"method calls your block whether script evaluation completes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"successfully or fails. The block has no return value and takes the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"following parameter:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"result: The result of the script evaluation, or an error object that contains"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"information about the problem that occurred. If your function body doesn’t"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"return an explicit value, WebKit passes "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" to your completion handler on"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"success. If your function explicitly returns null, WebKit returns that value"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSNull"},{"type":"text","text":" object."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}],"name":"completionHandler"}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function is a backport of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"WKWebView.callAsyncJavaScript(_:arguments:in:completionHandler:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method. It relies on"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the script message handler to pass the result or error to the native side"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"asynchronously."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"It differs from the WebKit method in the following ways:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"No support for passing "},{"code":"NSDate","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" as an argument."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Errors are not wrapped in a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"WKError"},{"type":"text","text":" object."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}],"name":"Note"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Don’t format the string in the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"functionBody"},{"type":"text","text":" parameter as a function-like callable"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"object, as you would in pure JavaScript. Instead, put only the body of the function in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"string. For example, the following string shows a valid function body that takes x, y, and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"z arguments and returns a result."}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["return x ? y : z"],"syntax":"js"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If your JavaScript code returns an object with a callable "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"then"},{"type":"text","text":" property, the function"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"calls that property on the resulting object and waits for its resolution. If resolution"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"succeeds, the function passes the resulting object to your completion handler. If"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"resolution fails, the function returns an error to your completion handler."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Because this method calls your JavaScript code asynchronously, you can call ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"await"},{"text":" on","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"objects with a then property inside your function body. The following code example","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"illustrates this technique.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["var p = new Promise(function (f) {","  window.setTimeout(\"f(42)\", 1000);","});","await p;","return p;"],"syntax":"js"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit","doc:\/\/Braze\/docume